1. Linux or macOS: Using Cron

Cron is a time-based job scheduler. To set it up, you’ll use the "crontab" (cron table).

Open your terminal.

Type crontab -e to open your cron file.

Add the following line at the very bottom:

Bash
0 * * * * /usr/bin/python3 /absolute/path/to/your_script.py
Breaking down the syntax:

0 * * * *: This tells the system to run the script at the 0th minute of every hour.

/usr/bin/python3: This is the absolute path to your Python executable (find yours by typing which python3 in the terminal).

/absolute/path/to/your_script.py: The full path to where you saved the code.
